    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Offering a museum-grade 2004 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the legendary S54B32 3.2L inline-six. This high-revving power plant utilizes six individual throttle bodies and a dual-VANOS variable valve timing system, all functioning within factory tolerances. Power is delivered through a precise Getrag 420G 6-speed manual gearbox to a limited-slip M Variable Differential Lock. This chassis has undergone preventative subframe reinforcement and a comprehensive VANOS overhaul to ensure long-term structural and mechanical integrity. The suspension architecture remains tight with refreshed bushings and dampers, preserving the car's celebrated 50/50 weight distribution and tactile steering feedback. The exterior finish is flawless, showing no evidence of rock chips or clear coat failure, while the interior maintains its original Nappa leather supple texture. A turn-key example for the purist.",
